object-model.content:
The contents of [@font-face](#at-font-face-rule) and [@font-feature-values](#at-ruledef-font-feature-values) rules
can be accessed via the following extensions to the CSS Object Model.


 Tests


 [idlharness.html](https://wpt.fyi/results/css/css-fonts/idlharness.html) [(live test)](http://wpt.live/css/css-fonts/idlharness.html) [(source)](https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/blob/master/css/css-fonts/idlharness.html)



 12.1. The CSSFontFaceRule interface[](#om-fontface)

The **CSSFontFaceRule** interface represents a [<@font-face>](#at-font-face-rule) rule.

```
[[Exposed](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#Exposed)=Window]
interface CSSFontFaceRule : [CSSRule](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssrule) {
 readonly attribute [CSSStyleDeclaration](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssstyledeclaration) style;
};

```

 12.2. The CSSFontFeatureValuesRule interface[](#om-fontfeaturevalues)

The CSSRule interface is extended as follows:

```
partial interface [CSSRule](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssrule) { const [unsigned short](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-unsigned-short) FONT_FEATURE_VALUES_RULE = 14;
};
```


The **CSSFontFeatureValuesRule** interface represents a @font-feature-values rule.

```
[[Exposed](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#Exposed)=Window]
interface CSSFontFeatureValuesRule : [CSSRule](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssrule) {
 attribute [CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring) fontFamily;
 readonly attribute [CSSFontFeatureValuesMap](#cssfontfeaturevaluesmap) annotation;
 readonly attribute [CSSFontFeatureValuesMap](#cssfontfeaturevaluesmap) ornaments;
 readonly attribute [CSSFontFeatureValuesMap](#cssfontfeaturevaluesmap) stylistic;
 readonly attribute [CSSFontFeatureValuesMap](#cssfontfeaturevaluesmap) swash;
 readonly attribute [CSSFontFeatureValuesMap](#cssfontfeaturevaluesmap) characterVariant;
 readonly attribute [CSSFontFeatureValuesMap](#cssfontfeaturevaluesmap) styleset;
};

[[Exposed](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#Exposed)=Window]
interface CSSFontFeatureValuesMap {
 maplike<[CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring), [sequence](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-sequence)<[unsigned long](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-unsigned-long)>>;
 [undefined](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-undefined) set([CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring) featureValueName,
 ([unsigned long](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-unsigned-long) or [sequence](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-sequence)<[unsigned long](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-unsigned-long)>) values);
};

```


 fontFamily of type CSSOMString 
 The list of one or more font families for which a given set of feature values is defined.
 value maps of type CSSFontFeatureValuesMap, readonly 
 Maps of feature values associated with feature value names for a given [font-variant-alternates](#propdef-font-variant-alternates) value type


Each value map attribute of CSSFontFeatureValuesRule reflects the values
defined via a corresponding feature value block.
Thus, the annotation attribute
contains the values contained within a @annotation feature value block, the ornaments attribute contains the
values contained with a @ornaments feature value block and so forth.


The CSSFontFeatureValuesMap interface uses the [default map class methods](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#js-maplike) but the set method has different behavior. It takes a sequence of unsigned integers and
associates it with a given featureValueName. The method
behaves the same as the default map class method
except that a single unsigned long value is treated as a sequence of a
single value. The method throws an exception if an invalid number of
values is passed in. If the associated feature value block only allows a limited number of values, the set method
throws an InvalidAccessError exception when the input
sequence to set contains more than the limited number of
values. See the
description of [multi-valued feature value definitions](#multi-value-features) for details on the maximum number of values allowed for a given type
of feature value block. The get method always returns a sequence of values, even if the sequence only contains
a single value.

 12.3. The CSSFontPaletteValuesRule interface[](#om-fontpalettevalues)

```
[[Exposed](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#Exposed)=Window]interface CSSFontPaletteValuesRule : [CSSRule](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssrule) {
 readonly attribute [CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring) name;
 readonly attribute [CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring) fontFamily;
 readonly attribute [CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring) basePalette;
 readonly attribute [CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring) overrideColors;
};
```


The fontFamily and basePalette interfaces are parsed according to the appropriate CSS property syntax.

serializing.content:
13.1. Serializing font-related properties [](#serializing-properties)

Unless specifically noted for individual properties,
 the properties defined in this module 
 follow the principles of [CSSOM § 6.7.2 Serializing CSS Values](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#serializing-css-values).


 Tests


 [font-variant-serialization.html](https://wpt.fyi/results/css/css-fonts/parsing/font-variant-serialization.html) [(live test)](http://wpt.live/css/css-fonts/parsing/font-variant-serialization.html) [(source)](https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/blob/master/css/css-fonts/parsing/font-variant-serialization.html)



 13.2. Serializing font-related at-rules [](#serializing-at-rules)

Unless specifically noted
 for individual descriptors,
 the descriptors defined for at-rules in this module 
 follow the principles of [CSSOM § 6.7.2 Serializing CSS Values](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#serializing-css-values).


In particular,
 following the principle of shorter representation:
 for descriptors which accept a range of values,
 if the start and end values are the same
 (the range is zero)
 the descriptor is serialized as a single value, not a range.


 Tests


 [at-font-face-descriptors.html](https://wpt.fyi/results/css/css-fonts/variations/at-font-face-descriptors.html) [(live test)](http://wpt.live/css/css-fonts/variations/at-font-face-descriptors.html) [(source)](https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/blob/master/css/css-fonts/variations/at-font-face-descriptors.html)




 [](#ex-zero-range) For example, the rule 

```
@font-face {
 font-family: "foo";
 font-weight: 200 200;
}

```


would serialize as

```
@font-face {
 font-family: "foo";
 font-weight: 200;
}

```



Also,
 following the principle of retaining only the last-defined value,
 as well as the principle of shortest representation,
 multiply-specified tuples and multiple blocks
 are serialized as a single block
 containing only the last-defined value.


 [](#ex-serialize-same-font-feature-values) For example, the declaration: 

```
/* Repeated declaration names, and multiple blocks of the same type*/
@font-feature-values foo {
 @swash { pretty: 0; cool: 2; }
 @swash { pretty: 1; }
}

```


would be serialized as:

```
/* Canonical serialization */
@font-feature-values foo {
 @swash { cool: 2; pretty: 1; }
}

```

